#  EXP 4 (Advanced Conditions + Calculations)

### 1. Display the list of employees who have joined before 30th June 1980 or after 31st Dec 1981

```sql id="c1a2b3"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE HIREDATE<'1980-06-30' OR HIREDATE>'1981-12-31';
```

### 2. Display the names of employees whose names have second alphabet A

```sql id="c1a2b4"
SELECT ENAME FROM Employee WHERE ENAME LIKE '_A%';
```

### 3. Display the names of employees whose name is exactly five characters long

```sql id="c1a2b5"
SELECT ENAME FROM Employee WHERE LENGTH(ENAME)=5;
```

### 4. Display the names of employees whose names have second alphabet A

```sql id="c1a2b6"
SELECT ENAME FROM Employee WHERE ENAME LIKE '_A%';
```

### 5. Display the names of employees who are not working as salesman or clerk or analyst

```sql id="c1a2b7"
SELECT ENAME FROM Employee WHERE JOB NOT IN('SALESMAN','CLERK','ANALYST');
```

### 6. Display employee name with annual salary, highest salary first

```sql id="c1a2b8"
SELECT ENAME, SAL*12 AS ANNUAL_SAL FROM Employee ORDER BY SAL DESC;
```

### 7. Display name, sal, hra, da, pf, totalsal for each employee

```sql id="c1a2b9"
SELECT ENAME, SAL, SAL*0.15 AS HRA, SAL*0.10 AS DA, SAL*0.05 AS PF, (SAL + SAL*0.15 + SAL*0.10 - SAL*0.05) AS TOTALSAL FROM Employee;
```

### 8. Update salary by 10% for employees not eligible for commission

```sql id="c1a2c0"
UPDATE Employee SET SAL=SAL*1.10 WHERE COMM IS NULL;
```

### 9. Display employees whose salary is more than 3000 after 20% increment

```sql id="c1a2c1"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE SAL*1.20>3000;
```

### 10. Display employees whose salary contains at least 3 digits

```sql id="c1a2c2"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE SAL>=100;
```
